{"TopicId":146858,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Need more torque?","CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T06:57:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T06:57:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fOSKukO.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/fOSKukO.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T07:42:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow much torque does it have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T08:44:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222736568\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472629332\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145504\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sharpy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n59 minutes ago, Sharpy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow much torque does it have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n30\u002B5*7*2=100\u003Cbr\u003E\nElegant solution, however using 4 large reaction wheels give 120 with four parts. rather than 19. Yes its 4 times as long but you can hide other stuff in them.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T08:57:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222736593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472633066\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n30\u002B5*7*2=100\u003Cbr\u003E\nElegant solution, however using 4 large reaction wheels give 120 with four parts. rather than 19. Yes its 4 times as long but you can hide other stuff in them.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nactually, 30 \u002B 9(5*2) = 120\u003Cbr\u003E\nthere\u0027s 8 in the ring and the ninth is in the core.\u003Cbr\u003E\nyou get 4 large wheels\u0027 worth of torque in the same space as only 1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T08:58:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222736600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472633822\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139010\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xyphos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Xyphos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nactually, 30 \u002B 9(5*2) = 120\u003Cbr\u003E\nthere\u0027s 8 in the ring and the ninth is in the core.\u003Cbr\u003E\nyou get 4 large wheels\u0027 worth of torque in the same space as only 1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy mistake I thought it was 6 way symmetry not 8.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T09:01:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd how does that work out mass-wise? What configuration would give most newton-meters per tonne?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: lemme answer that. The small wheels have the worst \u0022torque density\u0022, 1 torque per 10kg. The two others have 1.5 per 10kg. So you\u0027d be actually better off stuffing that wheel with medium wheels as the medium wheel gives thrice the torque for twice the mass of small.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit2: ok, but not entirely in this form factor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022dab4CY7.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/dab4CY7.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis thing is 1.1 tons at 120 units of torque. 9.1kg/unit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is 807kg at 105 units. 7.6kg/unit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-31T09:23:05Z\u0022 title=\u002208/31/2016 09:23  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 31, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Sharpy\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T09:25:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoesn\u0027t fit, but an interesting resemblance to a wheel bearing \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T09:38:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if we\u0027re going to optimize for space, here\u0027s 210 torque \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022p6MAznR.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/p6MAznR.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m tempted to claw it to an asteroid, but I\u0027m afraid transport would be nightmarish.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T09:43:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222736622\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472636311\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145504\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sharpy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Sharpy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if we\u0027re going to optimize for space, here\u0027s 210 torque \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;snip\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m tempted to claw it to an asteroid, but I\u0027m afraid transport would be nightmarish.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRig an action group to enable/disable the wheels, then fly it out like an ordinary dead payload. Shouldn\u0027t be any harder than any other asteroid rendezvous mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T09:59:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA good idea. I forgot you can enable/disable the wheels through action group. Switching them on/off manually would be about impossible, and anything smaller than a full orange tank would be so twitchy I\u0027d go crazy trying to maneuver it in orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"X-SR71","CreatedById":108775,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T12:08:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhh! Great use of unused space there! Will definitely make an subassembly of that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-31T14:43:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you can \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E by rolling uphill that\u0027s a bit too much torque \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-01T11:33:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose things look like kraken bait.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest,\u003Cbr\u003E\n-Slashy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-01T15:49:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy personal favorite solution for \u0022need lots of reaction torque\u0022 is the \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eradially attachable\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E reaction wheels from SpaceY.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/90545-113-spacey-heavy-lifter-parts-pack-v1131-2016-08-01/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=1532724\u0026amp;embedComment=1532724\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-1532724\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmong other stuff, the mod adds two sizes of radially-attachable reaction wheels, one for 3.75m craft and one for 5m (SpaceY is all about big rockets, so it adds a 5m part size with some really big tanks and engines).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe design is brilliant.\u00A0 The reaction wheel is a semicircular thing that you can radially attach to the surface of a cylindrical part of the right diameter.\u00A0 \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:9px;\u0022\u003E(Or the wrong diameter, but then it looks kinda dorky.)\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0 It\u0027s designed so that if you attach \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Etwo\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E of them with twofold radial symmetry, they mesh nicely with each other and you get a single ring around your ship.\u00A0 (Looks really nice.\u00A0 He\u0027s designed the visual appearance so they have a similar paint scheme to the 3.75m stock parts.\u00A0 Fits in perfectly.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey produce a lot of torque (being big) ... but what\u0027s really nice about it is that since they\u0027re radially attached, you don\u0027t have to put them inline in your stack, which means you don\u0027t end up with a wobbly/floppy rocket and you can pack on as many of them as the height of your fuel tank will allow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, this won\u0027t help you if your stack is smaller than 3.75m.\u00A0 However, I find that\u0027s not an issue for me-- the only time I need such huge amounts of torque is when I have a big ship, which means I generally have a large-diameter part somewhere anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-01T18:00:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125662\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003E If you\u0027re feeling cheatsy, you can attach more than two and they don\u0027t Z-fight. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpacedCowboy","CreatedById":92106,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-01T23:06:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy on Kerbin would you want that much torque to begin with?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheDestroyer111","CreatedById":160216,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-02T09:07:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222738889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472771185\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002292106\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpacedCowboy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, SpacedCowboy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy on Kerbin would you want that much torque to begin with?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the picture in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, look at the mass displayed by \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E. It weighs over\u00A0a frappin 400 tons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-02T10:19:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222738889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472771185\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002292106\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpacedCowboy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, SpacedCowboy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy on Kerbin would you want that much torque to begin with?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAsteroids. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-02T21:31:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222738889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472771185\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002292106\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpacedCowboy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, SpacedCowboy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy on Kerbin would you want that much torque to begin with?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI shall now direct you to the link in my signature that says \u0022Project Intrepid.\u0022 I am currently launching a 94 meter long ship. That\u0027s not counting the lifter. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpacedCowboy","CreatedById":92106,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-03T02:20:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222739993\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472851884\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161505\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ultimate Steve\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Ultimate Steve said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI shall now direct you to the link in my signature that says \u0022Project Intrepid.\u0022 I am currently launching a 94 meter long ship. That\u0027s not counting the lifter. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes Master ! ,,, Just messin\u0027\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll CIO. Sounds interesting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}